2. Logstash Installation
  a.	Login to Server using PuTTY using your AD Credentials
  b.	Go to the ELK_install folder.

cd tmp/ELK_install
•	Use Zypper package manager and run the following command:

zypper install logstash-6.7.2.rpm
•	Check the status of Logstash service using the following command:
 
systemctl status logstash.service
•	Make changes in the logstash.service file - Change User & Group to root. ---create a logstash user
 
vim /etc/systemd/system/logstash.service
•	Use VI editor & make change in the plcs-jira.conf file.
 
Open vi plcs-jira.conf
Vi /etc/logstash/conf.d/plcs-jira.conf (Change Host, user & password)
•	Make a copy of logstash.yml file.

cp logstash.yml logstash.yml.original (Backup)
•	Make the below mentioned Changes in logstash.yml
vi logstash.yml
Uncomment loglevel: info
Change it to loglevel: debug
Pipeline.id: plcs-jira
Pipeline.workers:1
(Save the file)
 
•	Use VI editor & make change in the pipeline.yml file.
 
Vi pipeline.yml
Pipeline.id: plcs-jira
Pathconfig: "etc/logstash/conf.d/plcs-jira.conf"
queue.type: persisted
pipeline.workers: 1
pipeline.batch.size: 1000  --unit
 (Save the file)
 
•	Copy the SSL Certificate to Logstash Folder using the below command:
 
cp/tmp/ELK_install/intelchain.pem /usr/share/logstash/ -----/mnt/jdc/tmp/physical/logstash
 
•	Now Start Logstash using the below command:
 
Systemctl start logstash.service
  a.	To Check logs use the below command:
  b.	Tail -f /var/log/logstash/logstash-plain.log //LOGS

